<h2 class="gem-c-heading  gem-c-heading--mobile-top-margin  " id="details-title">Details</h2>


<div aria-labelledby="details-title">
  
<div class="gem-c-govspeak govuk-govspeak direction-ltr" data-module="govspeak">
      <div class="govspeak">
<p>If the <abbr title="United Kingdom">UK</abbr> leaves the <abbr title="European Union">EU</abbr> without a deal, there will be changes to SPC and patent law on the day we leave. This sets out those changes and their effect on <abbr title="United Kingdom">UK</abbr> right holders, businesses, and other organisations.</p>

<p>Leaving the European Union with a deal remains the government’s top priority; this has not changed. However, a responsible government must plan for every eventuality, including a no deal scenario.</p>

<p>This complements the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/patents-if-theres-no-brexit-deal/patents-if-theres-no-brexit-deal">technical notice</a> on patents and <abbr title="Supplementary Protection Certificates">SPCs</abbr> published on 24 September 2018.</p>

</div>
</div>

</div>

